{
  "text": "Diversion and illicit use of buprenorphine is the subject of a recently published research review [CITATION_1] . The review shows that buprenorphine, like methadone, is a commonly used substance among IDUs and people with a heroin addiction in a great number of countries all over the world. Two countries, Finland and France, stand out in this context. A study from Finland shows that buprenorphine is the most commonly used opiate/opioid, and that 97% of the people applying for OST have buprenorphine as their main drug [CITATION_2] . Studies from France indicate that a majority of IDUs either inject only buprenorphine, or are using the drug as part of a polydrug addiction, primarily in conjunction with heroin or cocaine [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "24579553",
